Package edu.cmu.cs.ark.sage.effects

A collection of effects that can be used to represent the different sparse SAGE effects (eta vectors) generating the observed text/features.

See: Description

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Effect
    This class is used to denote a SAGE effect.
    EffectSet
    This class stores a set of Effect.
    IntegerEffect
    This is an implementation of a SAGE Effect that is indexed by an int id.
    IntegerPairEffect
    This is an implementation of a SAGE Effect that is indexed by a pair of ints.
    NamedEffect
    This is an implementation of a SAGE Effect that is named, i.e it is indexed by a String.

Package edu.cmu.cs.ark.sage.effects Description

A collection of effects that can be used to represent the different sparse SAGE effects (eta vectors) generating the observed text/features. You can extend the base Effect to suit your needs.
Version:
0.1
Author:
Yanchuan Sim
